Robots Will Steal Your Job, But That's OK: how to survive the economic collapse and be happy is a book by Federico Pistono that was published in 2012. The author refers to the title as a hope for the future, rather than a strict prediction.
The book, initially self-published by the author, was later picked up by publishers internationally and translated in six languages. It became a best-seller on Amazon.com  and was praised in various publications such as the BBC, the Financial Times and Ã‰poca.
